CC  This model represents the oxygen-sensitive (anaerobic, class III) ribonucleotide reductase.  The mechanism of the enzyme involves a glycine-centered radical [1], a C-terminal zinc binding site [2], and a set of conserved active site cysteines and asparagines [3].  This enzyme requires an activating component, NrdG, a radical-SAM domain containing enzyme (TIGR02491).  Together the two form an alpha-2/beta-2 heterodimer.
